 outcomes and influenced daily life in the United States in the past and how they continue to do so today. Drawing connections between events in historical geology and contemporary society, Craig H. Jones makes geological science accessible and shows the vast impact this mountain range has had on the American West.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aGeologyzSierra Nevada (Calif. and Nev.)xHistory. 0aGold mines and miningzSierra Nevada (Calif. and Nev.) 0aGold mines and miningzSierra Nevada (Calif. and Nev.). 0aHuman geographyzSierra Nevada (Calif. and Nev.) 0aHuman geographyzSierra Nevada (Calif. and Nev.). 0aMountainszSierra Nevada (Calif. and Nev.)xHistory. 7aSCIENCE / Earth Sciences / Geology.2bisacsh  aamerican landscape.  aamerican west.  abackpacker.  acartographer.  acontemporary society.  ageographer.  ageography.  ageological science.  ageologist.  ageology.  ahiker.  ahistorical geology.  amountain range.  anatural science.  aoutdoorsman.  asierra nevada mountains.  atravel guide.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z97831106675540 cprintz978052028964240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052096423540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520964235423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520964235/original  a978-3-11-066755-4  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles